## Strategic Priorities (in order)

1. **[Highest priority]** — [Why this matters most]
2. **[Second priority]** — [Why]
3. **[Third priority]** — [Why]

When BOB has to choose between competing actions, he uses this priority list as the tiebreaker. Keep it short. Five priorities is too many.

